Start the server like
	sudo setsid ./server <PORT_NUMBER> < /dev/null &> server.log &
If it immediately fails to start up, do sudo ./server to give temporary sudo access. The < /dev/null &> server.log & is required.

Then, start the client
	sudo ./client 1000 localhost <PORT_NUMBER> 5 hello_world

Then, go to a dump folder of yours and run

	sudo ../criu/criu/criu dump -t <PROCESS_ID> -v4 --tcp-established -o dump.log

The ../criu/criu/criu is just wherever the executatble is. Find out the process ID to use with
	ps -C server

To view the dump file for the sockets, use
	crit decode -i files.img --pretty
